<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BF7F19A6017E9B7C7" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF846A3BF7F19A6017E9B7C7" blockId="127.[2059,2652,2849,3276]" lastBlockId="127.[1448,2653,3284,3474]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
Cytochrome-b divergence of 0-6% occurs between S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BF74E9A3B173CB74D" authorityName="Goodman, Jenkins &amp; Ratrimomanarivo" authorityYear="2005" box="[2226,2364,3170,3199]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tandrefana">tandrefana</taxonomicName>
and S. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF846A3BF6519A3B1427B74D" box="[2477,2599,3170,3199]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marovaza">marovaza</taxonomicName>
, indicative of within-species divergence, but it does not provide support for recognition oftandrefana as a valid species; additional research is needed. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF846A3BFA549AA21752B676" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF846A3BFA549AA21752B676" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398392" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398392" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398392/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" targetBox="[1445,2036,2857,3271]" targetPageId="127">
