<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7B6AC4FF8692491FEEBF03" blockId="128.[119,1327,293,1314]" box="[122,494,1040,1073]" pageId="128" pageNumber="887">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF7B6AC4FF8692491F00BF03" bold="true" box="[122,256,1040,1073]" pageId="128" pageNumber="887">Breeding.</emphasis>
No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF7B6AC4FF8492601A08BFB3" pageId="128" pageNumber="887" type="activity">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF7B6AC4FF8492601A08BFB3" blockId="128.[119,1327,293,1314]" pageId="128" pageNumber="887">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF7B6AC4FF8492601F64BF68" bold="true" box="[120,356,1081,1114]" pageId="128" pageNumber="887">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
A Malagasy Yellow Bat in a flight cage emitted broadband FM/QCF calls at LDC, with frequency containing most energy at 48-2 kHz.
